x4freetext: .Details of
Experiments.
The Self-Supporting Targets were Metals of Natural
Elements (100% OCCURRENCE OF THE ISOTOPE OF INTEREST)
Of Thickness in the Range 1-4 mg/cm**2.
.A Statistical Multistep Direct Reaction Theory.
A Detector Telescope Consisting of a 150 Mum
Silicon Surface Barrier Detector Followed by Three
Si(LI) Detectors of 5 mm Nominal Thickness Each,and a
2 mm Silicon Surface Barrier Veto Detector was Used.
Particle Identification was Achieved with a Standard
Del`Ta E-E Technique in Which Various Combinations of
The Detector in the Telescope were Used to Measure
Energy Loss and Total Energy of the Ejectiles.
